               <p>(The case stated by Mr. Knapp.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18041205-44-person600">
                  JANE 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18041205-44-person600" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18041205-44-person600" type="given" value="JANE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18041205-44-person600" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - Examined by Mr. Knapp. Q. Do you know the prisoner at the bar? - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you know a person of the name of Ann Smith? - A. I do; the prisoner and her were married in the year 1791, at St. Ann's, Westminster.</p>
               <p>Q. What time of the year? - A. I cannot say.</p>
               <p>Q. Have you seen 
               <persName id="t18041205-44-person601">
                  Ann 
                  Smith
               <interp inst="t18041205-44-person601" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18041205-44-person601" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18041205-44-person601" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             lately? - A. Yes, I saw her a minute or two ago.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. Alley. Q. Had you known him before you saw him married? - A. A very short time.</p>
               <p>Q. Are you sure that he is the person? - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18041205-44-person602">
                  OLIVE 
                  ADAMS
               <interp inst="t18041205-44-person602" type="surname" value="ADAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18041205-44-person602" type="given" value="OLIVE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18041205-44-person602" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - Examined by Mr. Knapp. Q. Do you know the prisoner? - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. Were you married to the prisoner? - A. Yes, at St. Martin's in the Fields, three years ago last Friday week.</p>
               <p>Q. Are you sure he is the man? - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>
